ack by 400.'),(396,'2020-07-08 14:13:46','','2','Margaret Kemble Gage','0','white','none','black','0','American Revolution',' ','male','SYRW401','1734–1824',31,0,0,0,0,0,0,40,0,'1','H','Mrs. Gage, wife of British Royal Governor Thomas Gage of Massachusetts Bay, was born in New Jersey and was sympathetic to the colonists’ fight for independence. Sources speculate that hours before Paul Revere rode to warn Lexington and Concord, Mrs. Gage secretly provided vital information to Joseph Warren about her husband’s military plans.  Although he never found proof, her husband suspected her of spying and sent her back to England shortly thereafter.    ','Turn one of your opponent’s Characters into a spy and steal 1000 of your opponent’s Attack points and add that to your Defense.'),(397,'2020-07-08 14:13:46','','2','Robert Newman and Captain John Pulling','0','white','none','black','0','American Revolution',' ','male','WARW401','1754-1804',32,0,0,0,0,0,0,300,0,'1','H','On the night of Paul Revere’s fateful ride, Robert Newman and Captain Pulling risked their lives to light the lanterns that would warn Revere and other Minutemen about the British army’s intentions of leaving Boston and whether they were going by land or sea. These two brave men ascended the stairs to the steeple of the tallest building in Boston, knowing they would hang for treason if caught by any of the British troops in the vicinity. ','INTERRUPT: They risk their safety to warn your citizens. Increase your Defense by 1000 for one turn.'),(398,'2020-07-08 14:13:46','','3','442nd Regimental Combat Team','0','white','none','black','0','World War II',' ','male','ARW2401','1944 - 1969',33,0,0,0,0,0,0,4000,0,'1','I','This American WW2 regiment was unique in consisting almost entirely of Japanese-American Soldiers as a self-sufficient force fighting in Europe. Its soldiers earned eight Presidential Unit Citations, 10,000 Purple Hearts, and 21 Medals of Honor, all while their families were in US internment camps.',