by rail.  This culminated on May 10, 1869  when the Union and Central Pacific Railroads joined their rails at Promontory Summit, Utah Territory.  The event was marked with the driving of a ceremonial Golden Spike.','The Golden Spike allows the player to move one card anywhere in the continential US once per turn for 5 turns.'),(507,'2020-07-08 14:13:46','','8','Sir Henry Bessemer','0','white','none','black','0','Industrial Revolution',' ','male','IN4081','1823-1891',18,0,0,0,0,0,0,80,0,'1','I','Sir Henry Bessemer was an English inventor whose steelmaking process established the town of Sheffield as a major manufacturing center. Bessemer had been trying to reduce the cost of steel for military ordnance, when he developed his system for blowing oxygen through pig-iron to remove the impurities. This made steel easier and quicker to manufacture, and revolutionised structural engineering. Bessemer\'s practice is credited with making Andrew Carnegie the icon he became.','CHOOSE: Increase your morale by 500 points or double the effect of any Businessman currently in play.'),(508,'2020-07-08 14:13:46','','8','Henry Ford','0','white','none','black','0','Industrial Revolution',' ','male','IN4082','1863-1947',18,0,0,0,0,0,0,100,0,'1','C','Henry Ford was an American industrialist, the founder of the Ford Motor Company, and credited with the development of the mass production assembly line.','The moving assembly line increases you productivity, you may play 4 cards per turn while Ford is in play.'),(509,'2020-07-08 14:13:46','','8','William Kelly','0','white','none','black','0','Industrial Revolution',' ','male','IN4083','1811-1888',18,0,0,0,0,0,0,100,0,'1','C','William Kelly, born in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania, was an American inventor. He is credited with being one of the inventors of modern steel production, through the process of injecting air into molten iron, which he experimented with in the early 1850s.','Kelly\'s steel production methods strengthen your people, increase your civilization\'s defense by 700 points.'),(510,'2020-07-08 14:13:46','','8','Nikolaus Otto','0','white','none','black','0','Industrial Revolution',' ','male','IN4084','1832-1891',18,0,0,0,0,0,0,80,0,'1','I','Nikolaus August Otto was the German engineer of the first internal-combustion engine to efficiently burn fuel directly in a piston chamber.','Play Otto at the same time as an Explorer and that Explorer discovers two new lands instead of one.'),(511,'2020-07-08 14:13:46','','8','Cyrus McCormick','0','white','none','black','0','Industrial Revolution',' ','male','IN4085','1863-1947',18,0,0,0,0,0,0,100,0,'1','C','Cyrus Hall McCormick was an Inventor and founder of the McCormick Harvesting Machine Company, which became part of International Harvester Company in 1902.  McCormick is credited as the \"inventor\" of the mechanical reaper.','The increase of food production by McCormick\'s reaper results in your Army\'s increased strength by 500 points.'),(512,'2020-07-08 14:13:46','','8','Robert H. Goddard','0','white','none','black','0','Industrial Revolution',' ','male','IN4086','1882-1945',18,0,0,0,0,0,0,60,0,'1','C','Robert Hutchings Goddard was an American engineer, professor, physicist, and inventor who is credited with creating and building the world\'s first liquid-fueled rocket, which he successfully launched on March 16, 1926.','Goddard\'s invention takes your ability to wage war to a new level, increase any one Army\'s strength by 500 points.'),(513,'2020-07-08 14:13:46','','8',' Francis E. & Freelan O. Stanley','0','white','none','black','0','Industrial Revolution',' ','male','IN4087','1849-1940',18,0,0,0,0,0,0,80,0,'1','H','The Stanleys started the Stanley Motor Carriage Company, an American manufacturer of steam-engine vehicles. The cars made by the company were colloquially called Stanley Steamers, although several different models were produced.','INTERRUPT: Any one card targeted for the discard pile uses the Stanley Steamer to escape to a new land.'),(514,'2020-07-08 14:13:46','','8','Internal Combustion Engine','0','white','none','black','0','Industrial Revolution','Invention of the Automobile','male','TE4081',' ',39,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'1','I','The modern internal combustion four cycle engine, fine tuned and perfected by Nikolaus Otto and Gottlieb Daimler in 1876, became the benchmark for automobile propulsion during the Industrial Revolution.  It later went on to be the basic blueprint for automobile engines still to this day.','The Internal Combustion Engine increases your mobility, you may attack three times per turn for the next three turns.'),(515,'2020-07-08 14:13:46','','8','Pneumatic Tire','0','white','none','black','0','Industrial Revolution','Invention of the Automobile','male','TE4082',' ',39,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'1','I','With the automobile growing as the new form of transportation in the early 20th Century many entrepreneurs sought to attach their fotunes to the invention. One pair of men were Charles Goodyear and Robert William Thomson.  Their development of the pneumatic (or air filled) tire.  Their fundamental design is still used in most automobiles today.','CHOOSE: Gain 500 morale or double the effects of either Henry Ford or the Internal Combustion Engine.'),(516,'2020-07-08 14:13:46','','8','Moving Assembly Line','0','white','none','black','0','Industrial Revolution','Invention of the Automobile','male','TE4083',' ',39,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'1','I','The Industrial Revolution was all about the advancement and expansion of industry in the US and Europe.  One of the most iconic advancements was Hory Ford\'s moving assenbly line.  Ford, a automobile manufacturer, used this invention to reduce the time needed to complete one of his \"Model-T\" automobiles from 12 1/2 hours down to 6 hours.  This concept in now used to make most manufacturered products.','The moving assembly line increases you productivity, you may play 4 cards per turn for the next 5 turns.'),(517,'2020-07-08 14:13:46','','8','The Wright Flyer','0','white','none','black','0','Industrial Revolution','Aeronautics','male','TE4084',' ',39,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'1','C','The Wright Flyer, often referred to as the 1903 Flyer, was the first successful heavier-than-air powered aircraft.  Invented by Orville and Wilbur Wright,  it flew for the first time on December 17, 1903 near Kill Devil Hills, four miles south of Kitty Hawk, North Carolina.  It\'s fundamental design is the basis for airplanes still to this day.','CHOOSE: Increase strength by 500 points or double the effect of any Character card which is a pilot.'),(518,'2020-07-08 14:13:46','2020-07-09 21:38:22','9','Miguel de Cervantes','','white','none','black','','Renaissance',' ','male','AU4091','1547-1616',7,0,0,0,0,0,0,100,0,'1','I','Miguel de Cervantes Saavedra was a Spanish novelist, poet, and playwright and soldier.  His major work, Don Quixote, is considered to be the first modern European novel.  It is also regarded as being amongst the greatest works of fiction ever written.  He was badly wounded during the Battle of Lepanto.','Cervantes inspires your citizens to dream and tilt at their own windmills, you gain 300 Morale points.'),(519,'2020-07-08 14:13:46','2020-07-10 21:41:25','9','Suleiman the Magnificent','','white','none','black','','Renaissance',' ','male','CO4091','1494-1566',9,0,0,0,72,0,93,1200,0,'1','I','Suleiman I, also known as Suleiman the Magnificent, was the longest-reigning Ottoman Empire Sultan.  Suleiman personally led Ottoman armies in conquering the Christian strongholds of much of Southern and Mediterranean Europe. He was later stopped by  German Landsknechts at the Siege of Vienna in 1529.','All Christian Spiritual Leaders lose their Land 300 strength points and 100 Morale when combatting Suleiman.'),(520,'2020-07-08 14:13:46','2020-07-10 21:44:10','9','Morte d\'Arthur','','white','none','black','','Renaissance','Arthurian Legend','male','DO4091','1485',41,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'1','I','Le Morte d\'Arthur, translated to English as “the death of Arthur”, is a compilation by Sir Thomas Malory of traditional tales about the legendary King Arthur, and the Knights of the Round Table.  Many historians consider it to be the foundational work of the romanticized, chivalrous, Arthurian style of literature.','The romanticism of Chivalry fourishes in your civilization, gain 300 Morale points.'),(521,'2020-07-08 14:13:46','2020-07-11 00:15:17','9','Dissolution of the Monasteries','','white','none','black','','Renaissance','King Henry VIII','male','EN4091','1536-1541',36,0,0,0,71,0,91,0,0,'1','I','The Dissolution of the Monasteries, was a set of administrative and legal processes between 1536 and 1541 by which Henry VIII disbanded monasteries, priories, convents and friaries in England, Wales and Ireland. He also appropriated their income, disposed of their assets, and, in some cases, executed the clergy.','At Henry\'s demand, all Spritual Leaders in play must be discarded and each discaded card causes its owner to 200 Morale.'),(522,'2020-07-08 14:13:46','2020-07-11 00:12:16','9','Sack of Rome (1527)','','white','none','black','','Renaissance','Roman Era','male','EN4092','1527',36,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'1','I','The Sack of Rome on 6 May 1527 was a military conflict between the mutinous troops of Charles V, Holy Roman Emperor in Rome, and many of the Papal States. It marked a crucial imperial victory in the conflict between Charles and the League of Cognac.  Many historians see it as the end of the Italian Renaissance.','INTERRUPT: One opponent is forced to discard one knowledge or technology card and they lose 300 Morale.'),(523,'2020-07-08 14:13:46','2020-07-11 01:22:44','9','Protestant Reformation','','white','none','black','','Renaissance','Martin Luther','male','EN4093','1517-1648',36,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'1','I','The Protestant Reformation was argueably the largest division within the history of Western Christianity, completely altering the course of Christianity.  Inspired by Martin Luther\'s 95 Theses, it is considered the foundation for all current non-Chatholic, non-Eastern Orthodox Christian denominations in the world.','INTERRUPT: Nullify the effects of any Catholic Character card.'),(524,'2020-07-08 14:13:46','2020-07-11 01:29:24','9','Spanish Inquisition','','white','none','black','','Renaissance','Ferdinand II and Isabella I','male','EN4094','1478-1834',36,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'1','C','The Tribunal of the Holy Office of the Inquisition began in 1478 by Catholic Spanish Monarchs Ferdinand II and Isabella I. It was intended to maintain Catholic orthodoxy in their kingdoms and to serve as a retaliation to the harsh, forced, religions conversion executed by Muslim Moors in modern-day Spain and Portugal.','CHOOSE: ONCE: Either gain 500 strength when facing a land with a Muslim character or gain 500 defense when defending Spain.'),(525,'2020-07-08 14:13:46','2020-07-11 02:05:17','9','Battle of Lepanto','','white','none','black','','Renaissance','Early Naval War','male','EN4095','October 7, 1571',36,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'1','I','The Battle of Lepanto, in 1571, was argueably the largest naval battle to date in history.  It had 500 ships and nearly 150,000 soldiers & sailors.  The Holy League forces, commissioned by Pope Pius V, took on the Ottoman Naval Forces.  Many credit the Holy League with halting the Ottoman from conquering Europe.','INTERRUPT:  Send all Islamic cards to the discard pile prior to a declared battle; the battle must be fought with out them.'),(526,'2020-07-08 14:13:46','2020-07-11 02:07:09','9','Mary I of England','','white','none','black','','Renaissance',' ','male','LE4091','1516-1558',20,0,0,0,0,0,0,500,0,'1','C','Mary I was the Queen of England and Ireland from July 1553 until her death. Her executions of Protestants caused her opponents to give her the name \"Bloody Mary\".  She was the only child of Henry VIII and his first wife, Catherine of Aragon, who survived to adulthood. Mary is recognized as the first English queen regnant.','Mary gains an additional 500